replyContent:
Hi.
Differences between free and pro are mentioned clearly in the app description.
Features available only in pro:
Game analysis (either by time or by depth) is not limited 
Configure engine options for any chess engine (Hash, Threads, Syzygy)
Import PGN files from SD card 
Set up a position visually
Advanced filters, Recent PGN in Game Explorer.

content: Well thought out pgn viewer with a full stock of useful features. I just picked up Komodo 13 engine from the play store here, and it's running real smooth with this app. The single most useful feature with this app, and the other similar app, called chess analyze this pro, is the ability to add games to an existing pgn file. Very convenient for keeping a single data base of all your online games. Having multiple pgn apps lets you keep several different games ready to review.
replyContent: Thank you very much for your 5-star review. I am glad that you liked the features of this app. Please feel free to drop me an email to jyce.solutions@gmail.com for suggestions.

content: I really like that you can analyze an entire game to find out what were your weak moves and blunders. Supports very diverse engines Stockfish, Lc0, Komodo.

As a chess instructor I find this app indispensable. It's a fully featured analysis tool that eliminates the need to drag a laptop around. It's actively maintained by the author who is very responsive to questions/comments. Definitely one of the best chess apps for Android.
